II. 6, 7.) In Caesar’s day the lituus, a kind of horn curved at the larger end like the butt of a pistol, was some· times used by cavalry. Its tone was harsh and high. It is not spoken of by Caesar. The Romans never had a regular system of music as we have, with different instruments playing
